---

## Per-Agent `settings.json` — Full Technical Analysis

### 1. Workspace Folder Location (Full Path Pattern)

```
/Users/pierredosne/dev/projects/my_team/workspaces/<teamId>/<agent-slug>/
```

Defined in `persistenceService.ts`:
```typescript
export const WORKSPACES_DIR = join(__dirname, '../../../workspaces');
// → /Users/pierredosne/dev/projects/my_team/workspaces/
```

Agent slug = `name.toLowerCase().replace(/\s+/g, '-')`

**Confirmed real examples:**
```
workspaces/team-architecture/archi-knowledge/   ← this agent
workspaces/team-architecture/archi-reviewer/
```

**Current contents of each workspace folder** (both agents have only):
```
history.jsonl                  ← live conversation log
history-<ISO-timestamp>.jsonl  ← archived sessions
```

No `agent.json`, no `CLAUDE.md`, no `settings.json` — nothing else currently exists in these folders. The agent config (`name`, `mission`, `avatarColor`, `workspacePath`) is stored in the **team-level** `workspaces/team-architecture/agents.json`, not per-workspace.

---

### 2. How `claudeService.ts` Builds the Tools Array

The exact code — **no hook, no abstraction, hardcoded import**:

```typescript
// claudeService.ts — top of file
import {
  TOOL_DEFINITIONS,   // ← single static import
  executeTool,
  ...
} from './toolService.js';

// Inside runAgenticLoop(), every iteration, every agent:
const stream = anthropic.messages.stream({
  model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
  max_tokens: 4096,
  system: systemPrompt,
  tools: TOOL_DEFINITIONS as never,   // ← verbatim, no merging, no per-agent logic
  messages: iterationMessages,
});
```

**There is zero hook** — no `getAgentTools(agentId)`, no config read, no merge step. The tools array passed to Anthropic is always the same 4-item constant. **This is the exact line to modify** for per-agent tool injection.

---

### 3. How `toolService.ts` Loads and Executes Tools

`TOOL_DEFINITIONS` is a **TypeScript `as const` literal array** — defined at module parse time, never read from disk:

```typescript
export const TOOL_DEFINITIONS = [
  { name: 'read_file',      ... },
  { name: 'write_file',     ... },
  { name: 'list_directory', ... },
  { name: 'run_command',    ... },
] as const;  // ← compile-time constant, never loaded from file
```

`executeTool()` dispatches via a `switch (call.name)` — every case is hardcoded:
```typescript
export function executeTool(workspacePath: string, call: ToolCall): string {
  switch (call.name) {
    case 'read_file':      { ... }
    case 'write_file':     { ... }
    case 'list_directory': { ... }
    case 'run_command':    { ... }
    default: return `Unknown tool: ${call.name}`;
  }
}
```

**No dynamic dispatch, no plugin loader, no file-based config.** But `run_command` provides a shell escape hatch, and `executeTool` already receives `workspacePath` — making it straightforward to extend.

---

### 4. What the Workspace Currently Contains

| File | Created by | Purpose |
|------|-----------|---------|
| `history.jsonl` | `persistenceService.saveHistory()` | Live conversation JSONL log |
| `history-<ts>.jsonl` | `persistenceService.archiveHistory()` | Archived old sessions |
| `CLAUDE.md` *(optional)* | You, manually | Auto-injected into system prompt |
| `.rules` / `rules.md` *(optional)* | You, manually | Also injected into system prompt |
| `agent.json` *(optional)* | `persistenceService.writeAgentConfig()` | Scanned on boot for auto-discovery |

**No `settings.json` exists or is read anywhere in the codebase.**

---

### 5. Existing Config File Mechanisms Per Agent

The **only** config files the server currently reads per workspace:

| File | Reader function | When read | Effect |
|------|----------------|-----------|--------|
| `agent.json` | `readAgentConfig()` | At server boot (workspace scan) | Restores agent name/mission/color |
| `CLAUDE.md` | `readClaudeMd()` | Every time `buildSystemPrompt()` runs | Injected into system prompt |
| `.rules` / `rules.md` / `RULES.md` / `.claude/rules.md` | `readRules()` | Every time `buildSystemPrompt()` runs | Injected into system prompt |

**No `settings.json` is read anywhere.** There is no existing per-agent tool/skill configuration mechanism.

---

### How to Implement `settings.json` Per-Agent (Exact Insertion Points)

Given the above, here is precisely where and how to add it:

**Step 1 — Define the schema** (in `toolService.ts`):
```typescript
// New: load custom tool defs from workspace settings.json
export interface CustomToolDef {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  input_schema: object;
  command: string; // shell template, e.g. "python scripts/my_tool.py --input '{input}'"
}
export interface AgentSettings {
  tools?: CustomToolDef[];
}
export function readAgentSettings(workspacePath: string): AgentSettings {
  const p = join(workspacePath, 'settings.json');
  if (!existsSync(p)) return {};
  try { return JSON.parse(readFileSync(p, 'utf-8')); }
  catch { return {}; }
}
```

**Step 2 — Merge tools in `claudeService.ts`** (the one line to change):
```typescript
// Before (line ~70):
tools: TOOL_DEFINITIONS as never,

// After:
const agentSettings = readAgentSettings(agent.workspacePath);
const extraTools = (agentSettings.tools ?? []).map(t => ({
  name: t.name, description: t.description, input_schema: t.input_schema
}));
tools: [...TOOL_DEFINITIONS, ...extraTools] as never,
```

**Step 3 — Handle dispatch in `executeTool()`**:
```typescript
default: {
  // Check workspace settings.json for a matching custom tool
  const settings = readAgentSettings(workspacePath);
  const customTool = settings.tools?.find(t => t.name === call.name);
  if (customTool) {
    const cmd = customTool.command.replace('{input}', JSON.stringify(call.input));
    return execSync(cmd, { cwd: workspacePath, timeout: 30_000, encoding: 'utf-8' });
  }
  return `Unknown tool: ${call.name}`;
}
```

**Example `settings.json`** to place at `workspaces/team-architecture/archi-reviewer/settings.json`:
```json
{
  "tools": [
    {
      "name": "lint_file",
      "description": "Run ESLint on a TypeScript file and return issues.",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "path": { "type": "string", "description": "File path relative to workspace" }
        },
        "required": ["path"]
      },
      "command": "npx eslint '{input.path}' --format json"
    }
  ]
}
```
